this week I had four different people on four seperate occasions completley stand me up. as in make plans with me and act all excited about them then leave me hanging all alone in the place we were supposed to meet or at home with no answer to a phone call when i call to ask "whats goin on?" or calling 6 hours later to tell me they decided that they made other plans. I HATE THIS because one day long ago I made plans with a loved friend and possible relationship that didn't work out and I ended up getting stood up. Not a big deal except that I didn't hear from the kid and knew absolutly NOTHINIG about what happened to him, why he stood me up, and what the heck went on for SIX ENTIRE MONTHS. I thought it was me or it was him or maybe something bad happened and a million zillion other things. Nobody could help me out nobody had the answers. it was a crazy time and months later, when things got resolved, I understood what happened and really, nobody could have done anything about it I guess. BUT regardless if I understand now, the situation of past still affects me today and especially during horrible weeks like these when people think it's no big deal to string me along and leave me all alone after even calling ME to confirm that we had plans (just like that one time so many years ago). This really hurts me and I guess it wouldn't be a big deal if it was only ONE person this week or whatever but the fact that it happened 4 times. wtf and i'm not one of those people who is just gonna sit around and mope because someone doesn't call me. I'll call them and be like hey whats up because I don't ever think that someone is actually gonna stand me up. I'm usually worried that something happened to them or wondering if someone just forgot. I'm an optomistic person and the first thing on my mind is very rarley the negative. This sucks even more though because I don't expect it from people and when it happens it crushes my heart. did you read that world? crushes my heart. and on top of that REALLY pisses me off. it's one of my only "things" when it comes to friendships and relationships. You GOTTA tell me if you aren't gonna come over or if you decided you weren't gonna meet me at the coffee house. The past had me broken for quite some time and although I have recovered, I sure haven't forgotten. Please stop reminding me how this feels, "friends". blarg. on another note, I suck as a person as well so I guess I deserve it.

we are all so vain and our issues are all so important. well, with that, I'll be headed back to Savannah tomorrow. I'm in some random airport in North Carolina that has free internet thank GOD and awaiting a flight to Atlanta so I can jump into my beloved jeep and do my favorite thing ever (other than a ton of things): roadtrip with Matt Hawkins back to savannah. I LOVE BEING ON THE ROAD. All I want to do right now is pack a backpack and start visiting my friends all over the USA. WHY AM I STILL IN SCHOOL?? AHH. I never thought I'd miss going to school. I know I'll miss being on the road with Rally Across America but I'm confident that Nick and Matt Bruce will do a good job with the cameras and whatnot while I'm gone... that's assuming that I even do a good job . Hopefullyy things will go smoothly and I won't have to problem-solve too much before I get to Savy. Hello travel, hello airplanes, hello roadtrip, hello life. i miss you, everyone.

Please forward the webpage on and tell people about the film! Donations to the Rally foundation don't help us at all because they go straight to childhood cancer research but a donation to Veritaz Productions goes straight to the documentary being made and helps FEED the film crew for the 3 long months that some of them will be on the road. 

WHOO!
xo

(taken from my brother's last article in his high school news paper)
  
 As a preschooler, I mistakenly thought that if I ran around the
jungle gym at top speed the wind would cool me down from the stresses
of previous playing.  One thing that I learned in high school (that I
probably should have learned in preschool) is that I cannot overcome
my present struggles by simply loading on more stresses.  Sometimes,
it can be the maturest decision to harness one's dreams, and settle
with a more realistic mediocrity.
       Around this time, the early yellow dandelions transform into a
fragile rhubarb-esque stalk, whose sole purpose is to rid itself of
what beauty it has left in the fuzzy seeds it contains.  A gentle
breeze can dismantle one's individual persona, but kids like me
appreciate the yellow infestation sprinkled throughout the front lawn.
       My final summer in which I can live as a careless teenager is here.
I can't wait to lounge for hours to the rhythmic motion of lawn
sprinklers, or just wasting time with friends circled around chopped
trees transcending into smoke.
       Dandelions are indeed the most efficient, and therefore beautiful, of
flowers.  However, one's beuty can be viewed as a weed to anyone old
enough to operate lawn equipment.  Fly a kite, trample the yellow,
and stay young.
--Michael Babbish--

I would like to make a quick dedication of lj entry to KATE MAHER(1) and KEVIN VanDUYNE(2) and KHALIL ALBATHY(3) right now because without them I would probably never have gotten into metal and hardcore music and if I had never gotten into the music, the culture, and the love of that stuff... My life would most definitely have killed me by now and if not, it would definitely suck and I'd be missing out on one of the single most wonderful types of music on the planet. muahahaha Thank you, Kate and Kevin _______footnotes_________ (1) Kate Maher, although not an avid hardcore fan herself, was there at my first ever hardcore show and helped nurse my love of the genre through undying support. If it was not for Kate's smooth talking and dedicated family, we would have never convinced my like-a-rock-when-it-comes-to-rules parents to let me go to Cornerstone Festival in 2000. Without you, Kate, I would have never seen StretchArmStrong play live at the Encore stage, Zao play the night away, and Living Sacrifice tear it up on the main stage with fire and smoke. Kate, you were there for it all. <3 (2) Kevin VanDuyne, a boyfriend for 3 years during high school, did his best to introduce me to hardcore music like NIV, Overcome, and Stretch, but had no success. Upon returning from Cornerstone in 2000, however, and experiencing great shows first hand for 5 straight days, I returned home to share this new found interest with him, along with all of his cd's. Thanks, Kevin for contributing to my exposure and providing your companionship once I finally, found out for myself how much I was missing. (3) Khalil, I think we can all agree, brought the art of hardcore dancing to the state of michigan. way to go kid. oh yeah, God played a huge roll too, duh. NIV? come on. hahahahahaa

So I went to Atlanta yesterday night for a few hours. Mattie, my ultimate roadtrippin brotha of another mother and I packed up and peeled out of Savannah around 3:30pm and Ended up in Atlanta about 4 hours later only to leave around 12:30am to return to Savannah. yea... haha

Why did I go to Atlanta? For a conversation. 

There's this band that has been on a huge tour for a while now. Their tour came to Atlanta and I haven't really had a chance to catch up with the guys in a while.

recap:
The boys in this band ended up on my front porch a few months back because they had a show in Savannah and no place to stay. We stayed up until the wee hours of the night talking about God and what we feel we are called to do in life and all sorts of other things. I had a great time with them and felt like I really connected particuarly with 3 of them.

ANYWAY, we have kept in touch (as much as a person can keep in touch with someone who constantly breaks their cell phone) but I really wanted to connect with them again before the summer. I really felt like I could count on two of them (especially this one) and I wanted to see if what I felt when we spent time together so many weeks ago was real or if they just thought of me as another person that they met on tour. (I didn't really think this but it was possible and i HAD to prove that wrong. scarry though when you aren't sure how you will be recieved) I dunno why but I felt like it was really important to reconnect. It's not every day you meet people like these two guys. It's hard to find Christians that are on the edge, taking risks, and doing what they love to do most. I felt like I could really relate to them and seriously, that's important. I don't get to meet people like that often and when I do, I want to keep them you know? 

Lauren is one of those people.
Nick is one of those people. 
Hawk is one of those people.

I don't care how far away a person is, what they do in life, or where they're from... those following the path the Lord made for them with boldness and hope are the people in life that are gems, it's sooo important to keep them close.

ANYWAY
I didn't get to see either of them the entire time I was at the show. I cought up with their merch kid who was is such a sweetheart and their front man who is also so nice and invitinig but all I really wanted to do was talk to at least one of these two other guys. The show ended and we still hadn't seen them so we figured they had already left and so, upset and feeling defeated, Mattie and I decided to get going back to the long 4 hour drive home.

On our way out, the man I came all of that way to see was on his way in. I cought his eye from the stairs and he eased away all of my worries about goinig there and being recieved as who knows what and not being remembered.  The hug he gave me was so strong I almost cried. Holy crap was it good to see his face and talk to him. I drove a long way just to do that. Turns out the other one had already left because he had thrown his shoulder out and had basically had a long week. This one, however, was still there and he was so encouraging. He was the main one I wanted to talk to anyway. I missed hearing his voice and couldn't wait to hear what God was doing for him personally in his life. He pulled Mattie and me outside and I got the conversation I was searching for. I also got the chance to tell him how much I enjoyed his visit when he was in Savannah and about how important I think it is for us all to keep up with each other. I wanted him to know I thought of him and the other as important connections in my life and that they are special and should know it. Thank God the feeling was mutual. Thank God I have a cell phone now so it is actually possible to keep up with someone far away (haha)

Who goes to Atlanta for a conversation?
hopefully more than just me. If you know more people like this please send them my way:)

why? because when God puts somebody in your life that you can connect with, learn from, be inspired by, and be a companion to, it is so important to cherish that person as a gift and to keep them as close as you possibly can.

here is my encouragement to you:
Go ahead and risk your heart. If you don't take those chances in life you will never taste the full potential  of friendship or be embraced by the full potential of love. Life is short... don't be afraid to live it. When you trust in God he will paint wings on your ankles and you will be able to sail steady through the risks life invokes.

i definetly ran out of the house without my keys today and, upon locking the door behind me on my way through the foyer and out our front door, remembered them inside. I turned around to go back upstairs to get them only to find myself locked out. Oh well I said to myself... no worries... i have a spare car key in my purse and I'll just chill out and run some errends and call casey to get her keys to let me in. I checked my purse to make sure my phone was there... it wasn't. Must have left it on my bed. Oh well, I can still get some coffee, right? I made my way through the small foyer we have to our front door and unlocked the bottem lock on the door knob, turned, and pulled. Getitng nowhere, I realized that the bolt lock was in place. You need the house keys to unlock the bolt-lock. Well, crap. I was stuck there from 11:30am to 3pm when Casey came home from class. I had class at 3pm. I'm skipping it. How on earth will I be able to sit still through another 2.5 hours of class after sitting on my butt and reading 6 pointless magazines cover to cover that my land-lord Jason hadn't picked up from the mail a few days ago for 4.5 hours. seriously, who does that. It didn't help that i was cold the whole time and it was raining outside. HOLY CRAP...I just looked at the sky and the horizon is black. storm of death like, whoa.

only because i know that nobody really reads this so many people wait for something big to happen to them in life, the big break, the big disaster... I'm always waiting for that big thing... and i think I want something huge to just HAPPEN becasue I want some sort of excuse to do what maybe I want to do. Or what I think that I want to do. Yes, I want to make documentaries but can I really do that? See, I'm so sick of waiting and really, i don't think a person should just wait around for something to happen.. haha. I just make my own stuff happen but still I find myself hoping that something will change everything very very quickly and force me to finally not have to worry about social norms, what my family expects, what society sees, etc. Somethingi taht will let me pick up my stuff and jump on a motorcycle and just start seeing what else is out there for me. dreamer. I want to: snowboard motorcycle around the us finish my cd start a new band and sing go on tour live a simple simple lifestyle simple BUT... the more i lean toward simplicity, the more complex I feel. all i want is holy jeens, a bottle of water, and some beautiful scenery... origional smiles and some snow here and there. all i want are connections with people... and real connecitons at that. where should i be at the age 21? Where will I end up? and somebody please tell me AGAIN why I am living in the flat low country of Georgia with mostly guy friends and no deeeep conneciton with many girls at all? I have a few tight girlfriends but none that really can fill those shoes you know? I miss some people very badly. oh life please don't dim, when i'm done and through I want to be as vibrant as a child realizing for the first time that he CAN fly.
